                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 89.3.00/1764.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Consul General at Shanghai telegraphs that Shanghai has declared
                    independence.</p>
                <p>Accurate news from the interior is hard to obtain, but four of the central
                    provinces are believed to have declared independence, and efforts are being made
                    to organize an independent government at Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
